<item>
            <title>[FELIX-1620] Script for running the created Karaf instances with a console</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/FELIX-1620</link>
                <project id="12310100" key="FELIX">Felix</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;When I create a Karaf instance using the admin commands it creates start and stop scripts to run this instance in the background.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I think this is really good for certain use-cases. But for other use-cases it would be important to simply launch that karaf instance with a console. In that case its important that the lifecycle of the instance is linked to the lifecycle of the console (so if someone exits the console, the instance dies). &lt;/p&gt;</description>
